      <bioghist id="aspace_a70faec0b63b2b076f88846b9b7bad58">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Loveday Yates was a security monitor in Sterling Memorial Library at Yale during the 1940s and 1950s.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_e6961b6e0a42ef2a5d40e939281c76f7">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection consists of pencil and charcoal drawings depicting scenes of Yale and New Haven, Connecticut drawn by Loveday Yates in the 1940s and 1950s.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
